Oct 22 2009 	Great Location!	We stayed at the Westland for a week celebrating my daughter's high school graduation. The location is great, very close to two tube stations, with a bus stop in front of the building, so getting around is so easy. Lots of things in walking distance. We loved: the Swan Pub; Cafe Diana; Pret A Manger. Hyde Park is across the street: great for strolling, picnics, Kensington. Walk to Portobello Road market on the weekend. It is fabulous! People, food, antiques, new and used clothing, so vibrant and alive. The hotel staff are very nice and accommodating. We had two rooms in the back, next to each other, and shared a balcony. Very quiet. Loved the church bells tolling. Our only complaint was with the car the hotel called to take us to the airport: we were assured that the fee was 50 and not to tip the driver. Upon reaching the airport, the driver asked for 53. I notified the hotel that the service may have changed their rates, or that the driver had changed the rate in order to get a tip. They responded promptly that they would check into the matter. I don't have a problem giving tips, but if I am told not to tip, I won't. All in all, a great stay at the Westland. It is on a busy street, so don't get a room in the front if you want quiet.	
Oct 4 2009 	Decent but...	I stayed at the Westland twice on a trip to England. On the outside and in the lobby, it is beautiful. But one must keep in mind how old it is. It is cosy, but cramped. Both my rooms were singles, with a 2.5 foot bed. The shower head in one room was broken. The decor and furnishings really need to be upgraded, but if you are in the mood, it does add to the air of the hotel. Other than the rooms, it is a beautiful place. Most of the staff were helpful, especially with directions. Beware though, it is not &quot;directly&quot; accross the street from Kensington Palace. As well, the restaurant only serves breakfast. It is in a great location, but the building is a behind a tall brick wall, so if you have never been there before and neither has your cab driver, you may have a little trouble finding it. It was fine for my first trip to London, but next time I think I'll check out the Ramada Hyde Park.	
