Jan 21 2009 	Pleasant Surprise	Our stay at the Westland was a wonderfully pleasant surprise. Our luggage, left a few days early, was waiting in our room when we arrived late in the evening. Our room was large, comfortable, and clean. The staff were pleasant and also informative and helpful when needed, but not intrusive. They saved us quite a bit of strain, as well as cost by arranging for a private car to take us back to Heathrow at 5 a.m. The cost was only slightly more than it would have been to go by tube and Heathrow Express, but with much less lifting and carrying of luggage. Breakfast was very nice - hot, fresh, tasty - we thought it more than adequate - and served by an attentive and friendly young woman. The location is very convenient to two tube stations, Portobello Market (as featured in the movie &quot;Notting Hill&quot;), Kensington Palace, and Hyde Park. We had no sense of apprehension while walking around the area, although we weren't out past about 00:30. All in all we had a very nice stay and would not hesitate to recommend the Westland.	
