Nov 5 2007	Great little hotel	On our first trip to London I wanted to stay in a hotel that had old world charm, and was in a good location. The Westland had both. The room was much larger than we expected, and the bathroom was great. Both were kept very clean. The hotel is small &amp; family run, so it had the charm I was looking for, and there were 3 tube stops within a 5 minute walk. We couldn't have asked for better. We felt the price was reasonable as well. The staff was friendly and helpful. We arrived 3 hours before check in, and had planned just to drop off our luggage, but they had a double room that was not being used, and let us have that room, which was much more than we expected.We only had two problems. I felt the pillow was extremely hard (so we went to Ikea &amp; bought a new one), and the free breakfast only included toast, which wasn't that big of deal, but it would have been nice if it was a little more substantial.Our stay was 6 nights Sept/Oct 2007.We would definitely stay here again.	
Nov 2 2007 	Great place to stay	Excellent value. We stayed 3 nights in early October. Great location in residential area on Bayswater Rd., across street from Kensington Gardens. Within 10 minute walk of 3 tube stations. Plenty of restaurants within a few minutes walk, and a laundry one block away. Our room, with balcony, faced Kensington Gardens, and was very quiet with large double-pane door/window. The room was large, by European standards, and very clean. The en-suite bathroom was also large, had combo bath/shower with plenty of towels, pressure and hot water. There is a bit of confusion in the breakfast room about full-English. If your room rate includes it, be sure to tell the staff. The continental breakfast is very basic.The reception staff was very helpful, with suggestions on transportation, eating, ATMs, etc. The manager, Shirley, was very helpful in getting us a refund on some long distance calls made from the room using an independent provider. Be aware! Would stay again in a minute!	
