May 9 2004	A gem. Great location.	We were surprised to learn that no one had written a review of the Westland Hotel. We stayed there in October 2003 for four nights. The hotel is located on Bayswater between the Queensway and Notting Hill Gate tube stops. Walk accross Bayswater and you are in Kensington Gardens. (Walk accross the park to Harrod's for lunch one day.)You are just a few steps from the Heathrow bus stop and can take the tube to Paddington for the Heathrow Express. On Saturdays, the Portobello Road Market is an easy fifteen minute walk. As we said, a great location.The hotel lobby has a charming living room atmosphere and the staff is very helpful and friendly. We lost a pair of glasses and the desk assistant worked for an hour to get us to the right person at the department store. They helped us find a one-hour glasses shop for replacement.Our room was a comfortable twin bedded room in the back which was very quiet. The bath was clean and the storage ample. Our view wasn't much but if you are in London, why are you looking out your room window instead of seeing the city?Breakfast was on the ground floor in an attractive room with excellent service. The breakfast was very good and certainly more than we needed to eat. The Italian restaurant on Bayswater toward the Notting Hill stop is excellent. We had dinner there twice during our stay.We would recommend this to anyone who wants a real London experience and will certainly consider it on our next London visit.	
